headline: The Incredibly Shrinking Pool of Publicly Traded Companies
summary: IPOs are back in style this year. But despite some high-profile debuts, more companies are holding off on going public or are getting taken private.

headline: EA Is Going Private in the Largest Buyout Ever, But This 1 Other Video Game Stock Is Still a Screaming Buy
summary: Electronic Arts is going private in a record $55 billion buyout by the Saudi PIF, Silver Lake, and Affinity, shifting investor focus to Take-Two, which recently hit an all-time high.
